{"id":49366,"date":"2024-02-08T15:43:42","date_gmt":"2024-02-08T10:13:42","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=49366"},"modified":"2023-09-08T15:43:45","modified_gmt":"2023-09-08T10:13:45","slug":"brick-wall-tiles","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/brick-wall-tiles\/","title":{"rendered":"6 Creative Ways to Use Brick Wall Tiles in Home Interiors"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Brick tiles are a new hot trend, and here\u2019s how to use them in your <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/interior-design\/\">home interior<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Brick tiles are a classic design inspired by the bustling subway stations of London, New York, and Paris metro. Dating back to the 19th century, these tiles have a rustic vibe symbolic of their raw nature. Rusted red to shiny glazed ceramic brick tiles, today, these brick-style designs are a style statement glamorously used in home interiors.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The beauty of brick tiles is their versatility in elevating both the indoors and outdoor spaces of a home. Tiles lend a luxurious feel to the space at a much lower cost than actual bricks and are easier to maintain. Want to add a sense of history to your home? Here\u2019s how to creatively incorporate brick wall tiles into walls, floors, and more.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Brick Wall Tiles for the Master Bedroom\u00a0<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>An inspiration from the red brick walls for underground metro stations, this bedroom is not your usual one. These elegant red and brown shaded brick wall tiles are elegantly minimal, yet make a statement. Blended seamlessly within a focal wall, they add textural dimension to the bedroom and create a striking first impression.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/08153624\/brick-design-tiles-for-master-bedroom.jpg\" alt=\"Brick design tiles in red and brown shaded add textural dimension to the master bedroom\" class=\"wp-image-49368\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/08153624\/brick-design-tiles-for-master-bedroom.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/08153624\/brick-design-tiles-for-master-bedroom-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/08153624\/brick-design-tiles-for-master-bedroom-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/08153624\/brick-design-tiles-for-master-bedroom-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Using earthy undertones lends a calm vibe to the room<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Get a Free Modular Kitchen Worth \u20b92 Lakhs with Your Home Interiors.\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/08183703\/designcafe-offer-free-modular-kitchen-worth-2-lakhs.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Brick Design Tiles for Study Room\u00a0<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Want to take your study room up a notch? Add a textured brick wall to draw the eye away from blank white walls. Thin rectangular pieces of brick-sized tiles are glued together to create a contrasting, busy effect in an otherwise calm room. Add framed pictures on the wall to amp up the ambience, and take a break gazing at your serenely chaotic view.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/08153716\/white-brick-tiles-for-study-room.jpg\" alt=\"White brick tiles for study room create a calming and contrasting atmosphere\" class=\"wp-image-49374\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/08153716\/white-brick-tiles-for-study-room.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/08153716\/white-brick-tiles-for-study-room-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/08153716\/white-brick-tiles-for-study-room-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/08153716\/white-brick-tiles-for-study-room-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">White makes a big impression when used with textures<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Red Brick Tiles for the Kitchen\u00a0<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Who said your kitchen had to be boring? In an Indian home, kitchens are the busiest rooms where the family joins in to spend quality time together. A space so important it needs to stand out, and what better than a wall that draws attention? The red brick tile wall backsplash with hints of beige and brown is the perfect combination for an elegant kitchen.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/08153707\/red-brick-tiles-for-kitchen.jpg\" alt=\"Red brick tiles for kitchen backsplash gives rustic look\" class=\"wp-image-49373\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/08153707\/red-brick-tiles-for-kitchen.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/08153707\/red-brick-tiles-for-kitchen-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/08153707\/red-brick-tiles-for-kitchen-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/08153707\/red-brick-tiles-for-kitchen-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Use plants adds a pop of green <\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Also, check out <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/brick-wall-kitchen\/\">Brick Wall Designl For Your Kitchen<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Half-N-Half Brick Cladding Tiles for Your Home<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Brick decor in homes is a hot trend, and this half-n-half brick tile look is sure to stun! Creating a textured effect, the brick wall is paired with wooden bars that fashionably add depth to the space. This lends the room a rustic countryside vibe while staying uber cool, which is ideal to calm the nerves after a long day.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/08153658\/half-n-half-brick-cladding-tiles.jpg\" alt=\"Half-n-half brick cladding tiles with wooden bars add depth to the space\" class=\"wp-image-49372\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/08153658\/half-n-half-brick-cladding-tiles.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/08153658\/half-n-half-brick-cladding-tiles-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/08153658\/half-n-half-brick-cladding-tiles-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/08153658\/half-n-half-brick-cladding-tiles-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Get creative with your brick tiles!<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Brick Pattern Tile Wall for Living Room\u00a0<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Living rooms are the best places to experiment with your creative ideas. If you lack space to play with different furniture shapes or accent decor, try this brick wall to create a beautiful focal point. A tastefully done living room reflects your personality and class. This shaded pattern tile wall in red with a show-stopper art piece is an excellent alternative to bulky stone walls and mimics the exact feel of a breezy outdoor space.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/08153641\/brick-pattern-tile-wall-for-living-room.jpg\" alt=\"Brick pattern tile wall for living room to exude a beautiful focal point\" class=\"wp-image-49370\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/08153641\/brick-pattern-tile-wall-for-living-room.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/08153641\/brick-pattern-tile-wall-for-living-room-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/08153641\/brick-pattern-tile-wall-for-living-room-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/08153641\/brick-pattern-tile-wall-for-living-room-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Use the wall to highlight your cabinets and pendant lights<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Also, check out <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/living-room-interiors\/brick-wall-design-for-living-room\/\">Brick Wall Designs For Living Room<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Brick Style Tiles for the Patio\u00a0<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Create a vintage blue brick-style wall in your front patio for a striking first impression. The combination of outdoor furniture, a small stream-like fountain, ambient lighting and the cool breeze whiffing into the space makes it a perfect spot to relax with friends and family.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/08153633\/brick-design-wall-tiles-for-patio.jpg\" alt=\"Brick design wall tiles for patio\" class=\"wp-image-49369\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/08153633\/brick-design-wall-tiles-for-patio.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/08153633\/brick-design-wall-tiles-for-patio-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/08153633\/brick-design-wall-tiles-for-patio-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/08153633\/brick-design-wall-tiles-for-patio-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Create hooves within the brick tile wall to add space for lights<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Personalied home interiors for all tastes and budget\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/27115725\/personalied-home-interiors-for-all-tastes-and-budget-scaled.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Brick tiles are an easier and more affordable decor than real bulky bricks. These creative ideas allow you to experiment with the size, colour, and room in question as you design a home to WOW! Want more out-of-the-box ideas? Reach out to us at <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/\">DesignCafe<\/a> for all your home design needs.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Explore, More About<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/brick-wall-designs\/\">Brick Wall Desings<\/a><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/brick-wall-cladding-ideas\/\">Brick Wall Cladding Ideas<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">FAQs on Brick Wall Tiles<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>1. Are there any maintenance requirements for brick tiles?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Like any other tiles, brick tiles have an easy-to-clean surface. Brush, dust, or clean the tiles to remove any marks or stains.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>2. Can brick tiles be installed over existing surfaces?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can, but installing new tiles over an existing surface is not advisable because this leads to an inaccurate finish and loosening of new tiles.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>3. Can brick tiles be cut or shaped to fit specific spaces or designs?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Yes, brick tiles can be cut to fit specific spaces and designs, but always get professional help. You can injure yourself in the process or crack the tile when you try to do it without the right machinery.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>4. Are there any environmental benefits to using brick tiles?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Brick tiles do not contain any chemical or toxic components, making them an environment-friendly option.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>5. How do brick tiles compare to traditional brick walls in terms of installation?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Brick tiles, as compared to traditional brick walls, are much easier to install. Conventional bricks are laid in mortar and stacked one after the other, making it a time-consuming and expensive process. Brick tiles, however, are like installing any other tile applied directly to the surface or wall.<\/p>\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row blog-form\">\n\t<div class=\"offset-lg-3 col-lg-6 bg-light\">\n<fieldset class=\"field-set\">\n<!-- <legend align=\"left\"> -->\n                    \n    <h3 class=\"widget-title text-dark text-center mb-0\">Looking For Functional Interior Designs?<\/h3>\n  \n \n     <p class=\"text-center text-dark mt-0\"> Get 20% extra space with smart solutions<\/p>\n    <!-- <\/legend> -->\n<form id=\"blogContactUsFormMain\" action=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/get_quote_action.php\" method=\"post\"\n    novalidate=\"novalidate\">\n    <div class=\"form-group\">\n        <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\"  name=\"your-name\" placeholder=\"Enter your name*\" \/>\n        <!-- <span cl